_description: ‘A sheath’, a double-entendre riddle — two couplets

CULDd575.Transcription:
I haue a hole aboue my knee& pricked yt was & pricked
                    shalbe&yet yt is not sore&yet yt shalbe pricked
                    more
CULDd575.Note:
‘sheath’ written to right. Formerly on a flyleaf of Formerly
                    on a flyleaf of Cambridge UK,  Cambridge University Library Dd.5.76.
